<div id="review_432136394" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/432136394" />
    <a title="Spmsu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13538146-spmsu"><img alt="Spmsu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1356112037p2/13538146.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/432136394?book_show_action=true">Oct 11, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Spmsu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Spmsu" href="/user/show/13538146-spmsu">Spmsu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer432136394" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8250083243580826461"> They Cage The Amimals At Night. Genre: Memoir By: Jennings Michael Burch<br/><br/> This book is a tragic book about a boy, named Jennings Michael Burch. He is in and out of orphanages, foster homes,, and institutions over a four year period. It is based in mostly Brooklyn, New York. While he is in and out of orphanages, his mother is in and out of hospitals. She is dealing with physical and mental illness. He feels left out and alone. He has to deal with the physical abuse of the hands of strangers. But </span>
  <span id="freeText8250083243580826461" style="display:none"> They Cage The Amimals At Night. Genre: Memoir By: Jennings Michael Burch<br /><br /> This book is a tragic book about a boy, named Jennings Michael Burch. He is in and out of orphanages, foster homes,, and institutions over a four year period. It is based in mostly Brooklyn, New York. While he is in and out of orphanages, his mother is in and out of hospitals. She is dealing with physical and mental illness. He feels left out and alone. He has to deal with the physical abuse of the hands of strangers. But he is unrelenting through out the time period. <br /> I personally thought that this book was amazing. It had the power to make you cry, and remember that this is a memoir, a true story. This happened to many children of that time period, and sadly still happens in some countries. This book ripped my heart apart, then mended it back together. Through all the ups and downs of this child's life, he was truly hopeful. I would recommend this book to people who would enjoy a page turner that warmes your heart.<br /><br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="8250083243580826461" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


